  m_Name: u9_Hivemind
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  entityName: 
  entitySprite: {fileID: 21300000, guid: fa5dfd096c6e61742a7b552d75de9656, type: 3}
  introduction:
  - Finally, intelligent life.
  actionSpeakFeedback:
  - "Though it seems your awareness might still be somewhat limited\u2026"
  - We are here to enter the haven of individuals, what else?
  - We are numerous, but require little sustenance. We are sure the city can provide
    for us adequately.
  - "The Hive can finally thrive, now that we no longer have to delegate so many
    units to protection, air filtering, nutrient extraction\u2026"
  - So many of us were sacrificed just to get here. So many resources were consumed
    in producing their replacements. But at last our unit replacement rate shall
    reach acceptable levels.
  - "Can you believe the amount of junk floating in the air outside your settlement?
    Units accumulated so much filth that they couldn\u2019t even be broken down and
    repurposed."
  - Such a waste of perfectly good energy, and in such trying times, too.
  - We await the stabilisation of our numbers eagerly.
  - "It\u2019s suspended a meter or so off the ground. I can see right through it,
    but it still casts a shadow. In the overhead lighting, I think I see a pattern
    on its surface. When I reach out to try and touch it, tiny particles sprint away
    from my hand, only to return to their original place as soon as I pull back.
    I try again, but there appears to be no way for me to make contact with it."
  actionPokeFeedback:
  - We can feel the clean air already.
